[1]
Date: Fri 7 Dec 2012
Source: Edmonton Journal [edited]
http://www.edmontonjournal.com/health/Legionnaires+disease+outbreak+Calgary+area+spurs+probe/7668263/story.html


Alberta Health Services [AHS] says it is investigating an outbreak of Legionnaires' disease in the Calgary area. Six cases have been reported so far, AHS said.

The agency is holding a news conference later today [7 Dec 2012] but says its investigation is focusing on finding potential sources of exposure to the bacteria, _Legionella_, which cause Legionnaires' disease.

The disease leads to a severe, sometimes fatal form of pneumonia. It is contracted through inhalation of contaminated water droplets and is not known to be transmitted from person to person.

[Byline: David Blackwell]

